163. 17. cum ad Peloponnesum classem appulisset. This is evidently an error ; nothing is known of an expedition of Dionysius to the Poloponnesus. The occasion of the error was the sui-name Olympii, which Cicero referred to Olympia in Elis. But there were temples of the Olym- pian Jupiter in many other places, even in Syracuse where this story is located by Aelian. V. H., I, 20.
